Two weeks after taking an overdose of opioids, American singer, Demi Lovato has issued a statement concerning her fight against drug addiction. The 25-year-old star who has agreed to go to rehab thanked everyone who supported her during this trying times and has said that she “will keep on fighting”. TMZ reports that her team is bent on cutting ties with everyone who is a bad influence on her life including a distant relative. See her post below: A post shared by Demi Lovato (@ddlovato) on Aug 5, 2018 at 1:53pm PDT 